SIMPLE: selfish
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Selfish
<hw>Self"ish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Caring
supremely or unduly for one's self; regarding one's own comfort,
advantage, etc., in disregard, or at the expense, of those of
others.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They judge of things according to their own private appetites and
<qex>selfish</qex> passions.</q> <rj><qau>Cudworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In that throng of <qex>selfish</qex> hearts untrue.</q>
<rj><qau>Keble.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Ethics)</fld> <def>Believing or teaching that the
chief motives of human action are derived from love of self.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Hobbes and the <qex>selfish</qex> school of philosophers.</q>
<rj><qau>Fleming.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Selfishly</ent>⟦br⟧
